sentences: Kubeme kõhus asub ka naisel erinevaid struktuure.
Anatoomiliselt on see ala naisel teistsugune mehe omast.
context: The word 'naisel' is the inessive case of 'naine', meaning 'woman'. In this anatomical context, it refers to the female inguinal area or groin region. The Estonian dictionary definition shows that while men have a spermatic cord in their inguinal canal, women have the round ligament of the uterus (emaka ümarside) in this same anatomical location.
